<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.156/132.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 25, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The following reply regarding bridge has been received from the Cuban
                            Secretary of State: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Since the bill in question has been enacted by Congress and
                                    approved by the President, the latter has no means at his
                                    disposal for suspending its effect; but he intends to defer its
                                    execution for a reasonable period in the confident hope that the
                                    United States will promptly complete its study of the matter
                                    and, if there are no objections to so doing, communicate its
                                    findings to the Government of Cuba.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>